---
import Container from '@/components/layout/Container.astro';
import PageSection from '@/components/pages/why-nix/PageSection.astro';
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout class:list={['bg-nix-blue-lighter']}>
  <Container class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 py-16">
    <div></div>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-start justify-center gap-2">
      <p class="text-nix-blue text-5xl font-black">Help!</p>
      <p class="text-nix-blue-darker text-xl font-black">
        Someone told me about this Nix thing and now I have even more questions
        than before!
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Don't worry, you are not alone. Many people have the same questions when
        they first encounter Nix. This page is here to help you get started and
        to answer some of the most common questions that people have when they
        first encounter Nix.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Container>
  <PageSection
    title="Why Nix?"
    pre="So your probably ask yourself"
    color="blue"
  >
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
      When getting in touch with Nix for the first time, many people have many
      questions and that is for good reason. Nix is a powerful tool that can be
      used in many different ways. But with power comes complexity. Let's
      explore some of the most common questions and concerns that people have
      when they first encounter Nix.
    </p>
  </PageSection>
  <PageSection pre="But first of all" title="Who is nix?" color="white">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
        While many projects would start explaining what they are, we want to
        first of all introduce the part of nix <b>you</b> will be working with: the
        Nix community. The Nix community is a diverse group of people from all over
        the world, with different backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. We
        are united by our passion for declarativity and reproducability and our desire
        to make it better for everyone. We are a welcoming and inclusive community,
        and we encourage you to get involved!
      </p>
      <span> This could be a nice spot for a community photo </span>
    </div>
  </PageSection>
  <PageSection
    pre="Examples are great, so"
    title="You may already know"
    color="blue"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Docker, Dev/Container…</h3>
        <p>...</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">YAML/JSON, HCL, CUE…</h3>
        <p>...</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Bazel, Buck…</h3>
        <p>...</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">GPF, homebrew, pacman, choco/rate…</h3>
        <p>...</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </PageSection>
  <PageSection
    pre="That's all great, but"
    title="How well does it work with"
    color="white"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">... My Codebase?</h3>
        <p>...</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">... My Operating System?</h3>
        <p>...</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">... My Hardware?</h3>
        <p>...</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </PageSection>
  <PageSection pre="And what about" title="The costs?" color="blue">
    <span>
      Nix as a tool is free and open source software, but there are costs
      associated with using it. These costs can be divided into two categories:
      - Training - Storage/CI time
    </span>
  </PageSection>
  <PageSection
    pre="But as with any tool"
    title="There are some Risks"
    color="blue"
  >
    <ul>
      <li>Talent pool</li>
      <li>Supply chain security</li>
      <li>Packaging overhead</li>
    </ul>
  </PageSection>
  <PageSection
    pre="But once you are in it"
    title="There are many benefits"
    color="white"
  >
    Long-term savings (time/toil/money/computational resources)? Job
    security/attractiveness for talent Availability Uniformity Control,
    Customisation Auditability
  </PageSection>
  <PageSection
    pre="With all that said, let's show some"
    title="Use Cases"
    color="blue"
  >
    - Share reproducible development environments etc.
  </PageSection>
</Layout>
